<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Jimette on 02-02-2002 10:54 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">It's the way MMORPG's are going. Verant, as usual, has taken ideas from other games and applied it to their own. 

Here, they have just taken the concept from [URL=http://www.project-entropia.com/]http://www.project-entropia.com/[/URL]  and added that to it's experience with e-bay, that some people are willing to throw large amounts of cash at games to make themselves superior to othres.

The thing that is really, really worrying is this :

"Legendary Items  

In EverQuest Legends, truly unique and awesome new equipment [b][i]will be introduced prior to their release on our other servers[/i][/b]. Be the first to find the War Helm of the Undead Buccaneer, or the Spectral Ring of Might, and discover the dangers that must be faced in order to wield these mysterious new items. [i][b]Some of these Legendary items will even be named after the first player who discovers them[/b][/i]. There is no telling what the Legends Team will come up with, or where these items will be discovered, but rest assured that there will be loads of new great new items showing up on [i][b]EQ Legends first.[/b][/i]"

So, lets say a guild forms on the server, and calls themselves "UberYoo", lead by "Angryman Housekicker". They play all day, and rapidly come to own the server

Doesn't this mean that the Live servers will start getting "Short Sword of the Angryman" "UberYoo's Robe of 37333" "Housekickers Helm" with their name all over it ? 

In short, not only will rampant mudflation continue, but the sad individuals who discover the items will have their name splattered all over the live servers.

If Verant does this, then the live servers will scream about the interference with their game

If Verant does not do this, then the Legends servers will scream because their achievements mean less then nothing.

Edit : Bah, left a tag open

[This message has been edited by Jimette (edited 02-03-2002).]</TEXTAREA>
